quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  32,21,"We shall certainly make them taste the lighter torment in this life before the greater punishment of the hereafter, so that they may return to the Right Way"
  32,22,Who could be more unjust than the one who is reminded of the revelations of his Lord and he turns away from them? Surely We shall take vengeance on such criminals
  32,23,We gave the Book to Moses - so be not in doubt for receiving this Book which meets the same criteria - and We made it a guide for the Children of Israel
  32,24,"When they showed patience, We appointed from among them leaders giving guidance under Our command so long as they continued to have faith in Our revelations"
  32,25,"Surely your Lord will decide between them, on the Day of Resurrection, concerning those matters wherein they differ among themselves"
  32,26,Do they not learn a lesson from the historical events of how many generations We have destroyed before them in whose dwelling-places they move about? Surely there are signs in this. Do they not listen
  32,27,Do they not see how We drive the rain to the parched lands and therefrom bring forth crops of which they and their cattle eat? Have they no vision
  32,28,"Still they say: \"When will this judgement take place, if you are telling the truth"
  32,29,"Tell them: \"On the Day of Judgement it will be of no benefit to the unbelievers even if they believe, since at that time they will not be granted a respite"
  32,30,"Therefore, pay no heed to them, and wait as they are waiting"